Mourners have arrived at Elundzini Great Place, in the Eastern Cape, to pay their last respects to AmaBhaca chief Thandisizwe Diko. Traditional leaders, politicians and government officials are among those attending the funeral service. Chief Diko passed away at an East London hospital following a short illness, last month. The 43-year old Diko is a well-known businessman and husband to the Presidency spokesperson, Khusela Diko. He has been described as a community developer. SABC News reporter Nkululeko Nyembe is tracking the story. In the video below, he speaks to one of those attending the chiefâ€™s funeral:  